DNS kya hai?

DNS (Domain Name System) internet ki phonebook hai.

Ye domain name ko IP address me convert karta hai.

Example:

Tum browser me likhte ho:

google.com

Computer ko google.com samajh nahi aata.

Usko chahiye:

142.250.190.14

DNS ye conversion karta hai.

Types of DNS Records
A Record

Domain → IPv4

Example

google.com

↓

142.250.xxx.xxx
AAAA Record

Domain → IPv6

CNAME

Ek domain ko dusre domain par point karta hai.

Example

blog.company.com

↓

company.github.io
MX Record

Mail Server

Example

gmail.com

Email kaha jayegi?

MX batata hai.

TXT Record

Verification

Jaise

Google Verification
SPF
DKIM
DNS Cache

Pehli baar

google.com

↓

DNS

IP mil gaya.

Ab browser us IP ko yaad rakh leta hai.

Next time

Browser

↓

Cache

↓

Website

DNS ko dubara nahi poochna padta.

Isse website fast khulti hai.

Famous DNS Servers

Google

8.8.8.8

Google Secondary

8.8.4.4

Cloudflare

1.1.1.1

OpenDNS

208.67.222.222

Vertical Scaling Kya Hai?

Vertical Scaling ka matlab hai:

Ek hi server ki power badhana.

Yaani naye server add nahi karte, existing server ko aur powerful bana dete hain.

Example

Pehle tumhare paas server hai:

CPU: 2 Cores
RAM: 4 GB
Storage: 100 GB

Traffic badh gaya.

Ab tum upgrade kar dete ho:

CPU: 8 Cores
RAM: 32 GB
Storage: 1 TB

Ye Vertical Scaling hai.

Horizontal Scaling Kya Hai?

Horizontal Scaling ka matlab hai:

Ek server ko powerful banane ki jagah naye servers add karna.

Yaani workload ko multiple servers me divide kar diya jata hai.

Example

Pehle:

1 Server
CPU: 4 Core
RAM: 8 GB

Traffic bahut badh gaya.

Server upgrade nahi kiya.

Instead:

Server 1
Server 2
Server 3
Server 4

Ye Horizontal Scaling hai.

Load Balancer Kya Hai?

Load Balancer ek traffic manager hota hai jo incoming requests ko multiple servers me distribute karta hai.

Nginx Kya Hai?

Nginx (Engine-X) ek Web Server, Reverse Proxy, aur Load Balancer hai.

Simple definition:

Nginx is a high-performance web server that can also act as a reverse proxy, load balancer, and API gateway.

Real Life Example

Socho ek hotel hai.

Customers directly rooms me nahi jaate.

Pehle Reception par aate hain.

Customer
     ↓
 Reception
     ↓
Room 101
Room 102
Room 103

Yahan:

Reception = Nginx
Rooms = Backend Servers

Nginx decide karta hai customer ko kis room (server) me bhejna hai.

Nginx ke Main Uses
1. Reverse Proxy ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

Client directly backend se baat nahi karta.

Client
   │
   ▼
Nginx
   │
   ▼
Express Server

Benefits:

Security
Hide backend
SSL handling
Logging
2. Load Balancer ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
        Nginx
      ┌──┼──┐
      ▼  ▼  ▼
   Node1 Node2 Node3

Nginx by default Round Robin use kar sakta hai.

3. Static Files Serve Karna

HTML

CSS

JS

Images

Videos

Nginx bahut fast serve karta hai.

Isliye React build bhi Nginx se host karte hain.

4. SSL/TLS

HTTPS enable karta hai.

https://example.com

Certificates manage karta hai.

Nginx vs Apache
Nginx	Apache
Event-driven	Process/Thread based
Faster for high traffic	Good for small websites
Better load balancing	Less commonly used for load balancing
Lower memory usage	Higher memory usage

1. Reverse Proxy
Reverse Proxy Kya Hai?

Reverse Proxy client aur backend server ke beech me baithta hai aur client ki requests ko backend tak forward karta hai.

Without Reverse Proxy
Client
   │
   ▼
Node.js Server

Client ko backend server ka address pata hai.

With Reverse Proxy
Client
   │
   ▼
 Nginx
   │
   ▼
Node.js Server

Ab client sirf Nginx ko jaanta hai.

Backend hidden rehta hai.

Benefits
✅ Security
✅ Backend hide hota hai
✅ SSL handle karta hai
✅ Logging
✅ Load balancing
2. Load Balancing
Load Balancing Kya Hai?

Incoming requests ko multiple servers me distribute karna.

Example:

              Nginx
                │
      ┌─────────┼─────────┐
      ▼         ▼         ▼
   Server1   Server2   Server3

Requests:

Req1 → Server1
Req2 → Server2
Req3 → Server3
Req4 → Server1

Ye Round Robin algorithm ka example hai.

Benefits
✅ Fast response
✅ Server overload nahi hota
✅ High availability
✅ Horizontal scaling support
3. SSL (HTTPS)
SSL Kya Hai?

SSL (Secure Sockets Layer) aur uska modern version TLS browser aur server ke beech data ko encrypt karte hain.

Without SSL:

http://example.com

Data plain text me jata hai.

Agar koi hacker beech me ho to password dekh sakta hai.

With SSL:

https://example.com

Data encrypted hota hai.

Example:

Without SSL

Password = ananya123

With SSL

x9A$!@7kLm#...

Sirf server hi decrypt kar sakta hai.

Nginx kya karta hai?
SSL Certificate install karta hai.
HTTP → HTTPS redirect karta hai.
Encryption handle karta hai.
4. Routing
Routing Kya Hai?

URL ke basis par request ko sahi backend ya service tak bhejna.

Example:

Client
   │
   ▼
 Nginx

Agar request hai:

/api

↓

Node.js Backend

Agar request hai:

/images

↓

Images Folder

Agar request hai:

/admin

↓

Admin Server

API Gateway Kya Hai?

API Gateway ek single entry point hota hai jo client ki saari requests receive karta hai aur unhe sahi backend service tak bhejta hai.

Simple language me:

Client directly backend services se baat nahi karta. Pehle API Gateway ke paas jata hai.

route check krke uss route wale server pr bhejta h jaise ek autentication ke liye h ek payment ke liye h and ek bla bla 

An API Gateway is a single entry point for client requests. It routes requests to the appropriate backend service and can also handle authentication, rate limiting, logging, caching, SSL termination, and request aggregation.

10-Second Interview Answer

API Gateway acts as the front door of a backend system. Clients send all requests to the gateway, which forwards them to the correct microservice while also providing features like authentication, routing, rate limiting, logging, caching, and load balancing.

Easy Trick to Remember

API Gateway = Smart Receptionist

🚪 One Entry Point → Client sirf gateway ko jaanta hai.
🧭 Routing → Sahi service tak request bhejta hai.
🔐 Authentication → User verify karta hai.
🚦 Rate Limiting → Request limit control karta hai.
📊 Logging → Requests record karta hai.
⚡ Caching → Fast responses ke liye cache use karta hai.
⚖️ Load Balancing → Zarurat padne par multiple instances me traffic distribute karta hai.

An API Gateway is a single entry point for client requests. It routes requests to the appropriate backend service and can also handle authentication, rate limiting, logging, caching, SSL termination, and request aggregation.

10-Second Interview Answer

API Gateway acts as the front door of a backend system. Clients send all requests to the gateway, which forwards them to the correct microservice while also providing features like authentication, routing, rate limiting, logging, caching, and load balancing.

Easy Trick to Remember

API Gateway = Smart Receptionist

🚪 One Entry Point → Client sirf gateway ko jaanta hai.
🧭 Routing → Sahi service tak request bhejta hai.
🔐 Authentication → User verify karta hai.
🚦 Rate Limiting → Request limit control karta hai.
📊 Logging → Requests record karta hai.
⚡ Caching → Fast responses ke liye cache use karta hai.


Difference yaad rakho:

Load Balancer = Same service ke multiple servers me load baantna.
API Gateway = Alag-alag services ko manage aur route karna, saath hi authentication, rate limiting, caching jaise features dena.

BAHOTT SAARE GATEWAYS BANA DO THEN GINX SE CONNECT KRDO VO TRAFIC HISAB SE GATEWAY PR BHEJEGA TOH ISS POORE CHEEZ KO MICRO-SERVICES BOLTE HAI

JAB EK HI SERVER SAB HANDLE KR RHATHA TOH USSE MONOLITH BOLTE HAI

JAB HAR SERVICE KE LIYE NAYA SERVER CREATE KRTA H USSE MICRO-SERVIES BOLTE HAI 

Interview Definition

Sharding is a database scaling technique where data is partitioned across multiple database servers (called shards) so that each server stores only a portion of the data, improving scalability and performance.

10-Second Interview Answer

Sharding means splitting a large database into smaller parts and distributing those parts across multiple servers. It helps handle large amounts of data and traffic by distributing the load instead of storing everything on a single database server.

